<br>
I can technically cast about 6 Ice Comets.  That's 6720 damage to the target, a tidy sum of damage.  However, if I do so, I have just aggroed the monster to a berserk level of hatred that NO force will pull off me, unless an enchanter happens to successfully mindwipe it.  I wouldn't even get the third one cast, it would be on me like white on rice after two casts, unless the monster is nearly dead anyway... which sort of negates the need to cast quickly and the point of having fast chain casting.<br>
<br>
Thus, aggro is a problem, it prevents Wizards from successfully carrying out their task.  Concussion is an aid with this, and there are some tricks to work around it, but this comes up in discussions where someone says &quot;nobody does damage faster doood!!!&quot; and it is pointed out that doing that damage quickly gets you turned into a red smear on the ground.  Thus, aggro is a problem. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ulifty.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lifty</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/24/01 4:50 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: absor/agro</span><hr size=1> I don't have a problem with agro.  Yes, I agro mobs, but only when I mean to (i.e. for exp in multi-groups, or to save someone else's ass).  I guess I'm the luckiest wizzy around, and it has nothing to do with skill.<br>
<br>
it is NOT the wizards job to yank a mob off the cleric.  that is the tanks/enchanters job.  if you feel you must do something, waste some mana and stun/root/concussion, don't yank it on you.<br>
<br>
i should have used the words &quot;unintentionally agro&quot; instead of agro.<br>
<br>
btw, use flux staff in kael for faction.<br>
<br>
if you are grouped and constant pulling and agro'ing, you are sitting oom through some fights instead of rationing yourself to an even amount of damage on all mobs (which is small comparitively to the melee's, our REAL problem).<br>
<br>
if you are multi-group raiding a single target, and need to empty a full bar, wait until its safe to get off one nuke, nuke, concussion, nuke, concussion, nuke nuke nuke...whatever.<br>
<br>
It's an art, and it is the MAIN thing you need to be skilled in.  You have to get to a level where you &quot;feel&quot; how much a mob hates you at all times, and how much hate your next move will make, and when.<br>
<br>
If I ever misjudge that hate, which is rare, i set at a distance where i can cast concussion before the mob gets to me, and have it hotkeyed.  In that rare scenario, the mob returns to the melee spot before they realize its moved. <br>
<br>
Fast Stun/root/concussion is another method.  Use your brains wizzies, this is what we are SUPPOSED to be able to do.<br>
<br>
I knew some people will argue this with me, but I suspect you are the ones that STARTED the trend of making wizards non-group friendly.  Those I mean that cannot control agro, and are constantly making the melee's run all over the place.  I wouldn't want to have wizards in my group either if that was my experience from them.<br>
<br>
Am (was) I the luckiest wizard around?  Or are there other wizzies out there that share my sentiment?  Or, are all the good wizzies already retired (like mine) and don't even read this board anymore (like I shouldn't be)?<br>
<br>
-Lifty Swifpocket/Rondeveron Stormsmith<br>
